sentence: Looking at units outstanding versus one week prior within the universe of ETFs covered at ETF Channel, the biggest outflow was seen in the iShares Russell 2000 ETF ( IWM ), where 3,600,000 units were destroyed, or a 1.3% decrease week over week.
Among the largest underlying components of IWM, in morning trading today Advanced Micro Devices ( AMD ) is up about 1.7%, and The Chemours Company ( CC ) is lower by about 0.2%.

And on a percentage change basis, the ETF with the biggest outflow was the PowerShares Dynamic Retail Portfolio ( PMR ), which lost 200,000 of its units, representing a 33.3% decline in outstanding units compared to the week prior.
Among the largest underlying components of PMR, in morning trading today Home Depot ( HD ) is up about 0.5%, and Best Buy (BBY) is up by about 0.6%.
